## Day 8 — Claude Code in Practice

### Concepts to Cover
- **Advanced Claude Code patterns**: Multi-file edits, running tests in a loop, git integration.
- **SKILL.md / CLAUDE.md**: How to encode project standards so the agent follows your conventions.
- **Agentic task delegation**: Breaking a large task into sub-tasks, supervising the agent.
- **Real PM workflows**:
  - Analyzing a CSV of user feedback with Claude Code.
  - Generating a PRD draft from an interview transcript.
  - Building a competitive analysis scraper.
  - Writing and running SQL against a local database.
- Knowing when to hand off to an engineer vs. continue solo.

### Practical Exercise
> Give Claude Code a real task from your backlog:
> e.g., "Read this CSV of support tickets and give me the top 10 recurring themes."
> Evaluate the output quality and refine the prompt.

### PM Takeaway
*Claude Code's power is proportional to the quality of context you give it. Invest in your CLAUDE.md.*

