## Quick Reference: Key Terms Glossary

| Term | Plain English Definition |
|------|--------------------------|
| LLM | A model trained on text that predicts the next token — the engine behind AI products. |
| Context Window | Everything the LLM can "see" in one call. Larger = more expensive but more capable. |
| Context Engineering | Designing what goes into the context window to get the best output. |
| RAG | Retrieve relevant docs at query time and inject them into context. Solves stale knowledge. |
| Distillation | Training a small model to behave like a big model. Cheaper in production. |
| Agent | An LLM that can call tools and take actions in a loop, not just generate text. |
| Eval | A test that measures whether an AI output meets a defined quality bar. |
| Vibe Coding | Building software by describing intent to AI, iterating without writing code directly. |
| CLAUDE.md | A project context file that tells Claude Code your conventions and constraints. |
| LLM-as-Judge | Using one LLM to evaluate the outputs of another. Scalable eval pattern. |
| Token | The unit of text an LLM processes. ~4 chars or ~0.75 words. Costs money. |
| Hallucination | When an LLM generates confident, plausible-sounding but factually wrong output. |

